<li><span class="caps">OMG</span>. The <a href="http://www.apple.com/ipodnano/">Ipod Nano.</a> Drool. Although it seems to have <a href="http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=05/09/25/1315224">problems</a> with the <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/4286294.stm">screen.</a> Though could it be just a bad batch? They even have black ones. They&#8217;re priced at 299AUD for 2G and 4G are 359AUD. I think I like this the most, but can I access it easily from my Debian system <span class="caps">CLI</span>? Someone looks like they&#8217;ve got <a href="http://www.tuaw.com/2005/09/19/carry-a-bootable-os-on-your-ipod-nano/">slackware</a> on it.</li>
</ul>

<p>I also found out that the <a href="http://www.russellbeattie.com/notebook/1008636.html">GB Micro</a> will only be in stores on the 7th of November in Australia. That seems to have an add-on which can play music and videos. Argghhh! But I am not fond of these SD flash memory sticks and waiting&#8230;</p>